metadata.subject: Mueller investigation strategy and potential indictment of President Trump

relationships.description: Weissmann is Mueller's number two lawyer in the Special Counsel's office
Trump was President and Flynn was National Security Advisor
Rosenstein as Deputy Attorney General oversees the Mueller investigation
Investigative team versus administration being investigated

analysis.purpose: To analyze and report on the Mueller investigation's strategy regarding potential indictment of President Trump for obstruction of justice
analysis.significance: Reveals internal strategies and legal theories being developed by the Special Counsel's office against a sitting president

concerns: Potential obstruction of justice by the President

notable_quotes: "This indictment could have been drafted without anyone being interviewed," said one source.
"Bob Mueller is all about limits and rules. Donald Trump has none and acknowledges none," said one lawyer who has worked with Mueller in the past.
"Might such an expansive claim win, yes. Should it win, no. But everyone knows the reality: weak presidents lose cases, strong presidents win them," said Ken Starr.
red_flags: Potential abuse of presidential pardon power

blackmail_indicators.description: No evidence of blackmail or coercion found in this analytical report

illegal_activity.description: This is an analytical report discussing legal theories and potential charges, not evidence of first-hand illegal activity

details: References to television appearances by legal surrogates
Mentions of public statements and tweets as evidence
Discussion of media strategy and public perception

public_knowledge.context: This appears to be journalistic analysis of the Mueller investigation, which was extensively covered in media during 2017-2019

analysis.summary: This analytical report details the Special Counsel's preparation of a potential obstruction of justice indictment against President Trump, outlining the legal theories and strategic considerations involved in what the author describes as an impending constitutional crisis between the Mueller investigation and the Trump administration.
